The Farmer and the Golden Eggs

One day, a farmer had a goose.
Every morning, the goose laid one golden egg.

The farmer was very happy. He sold the eggs and became rich.

After some time, he became greedy. He thought,
“Why not get all the eggs at once?”

So, he killed the goose. But there were no golden eggs inside.

The farmer was very sad. He lost both the goose and the eggs.
